
	 <h2>Install KDE 4.0 packages from the Debian experimental branch<img src="../images/download_64.png" style="float:right; margin:-8px 0 0 0;" /></h2>

	 <p>KDE 4.0 requires some software that is not available in the Debian 4.0 "etch" release.  Therefore, it can only be installed on systems using the testing & unstable branches.</p>
	 <p>Users of the testing branch may also need to enable the unstable branch in order to meet the requirements of KDE 4.0.<br />
	 To enable the unstable branch without upgrading your entire system, <a href="http://wiki.debian.org/AptPinning">see this page</a>.</p>

	<h3>Enabling the experimental branch</h3>

	 <p>To install KDE 4.0, the experimental branch must be enabled.  Add the following to <code>/etc/apt/sources.list</code>, then update APT.</p>
	 <blockquote>
	 <pre style="margin-bottom:0;">deb http://ftp.debian.org/debian/ experimental main non-free contrib
deb-src http://ftp.debian.org/debian/ experimental main non-free contrib</pre>
	</blockquote>

	<br />

	 <p>APT will not install packages from experimental unless specifically requested.  To install a package from experimental, run the command:</p>
	 <pre>aptitude -t experimental install <em>package1</em> <em>package2</em> <em>package3...</em></pre>

	<h3>KDE 4 meta-packages</h3>

	 <p>For a basic KDE 4 desktop, install </p><code><h1>Gabba</h1></code>
	 <p>For all of KDE 4, install </p><code><h1>Gabba</h1></code>
	 <p>For the KDE 4 development platform, install </p><code><h1>Hey!</h1></code>
